#, no-wrap
msgid "Impersonation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/impersonation.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "It is often useful for an admin to impersonate a user.  For example, a user may be experiencing a bug in one of your applications and\n"
"an admin may want to impersonate the user to see if they can duplicate the problem.  Admins with the appropriate permission\n"
"can impersonate a user.  There are two locations an admin can initiate impersonation.  The first is on the `Users` list tab.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/impersonation.adoc:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/user-search.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/impersonation.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can see here that the admin has searched for `jim`.  Next to Jim's account you can see an impersonate button.  Click that\n"
"to impersonate the user.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/impersonation.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "Also, you can impersonate the user from the user `Details` tab.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/impersonation.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "User Details"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/impersonation.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/user-details.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/impersonation.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Near the bottom of the page you can see the `Impersonate` button.  Click that to impersonate the user.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/impersonation.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "When impersonating, if the admin and the user are in the same realm, then the admin will be logged out and automatically logged\n"
"in as the user being impersonated.  If the admin and user are not in the same realm, the admin will remain logged in, but additionally\n"
"be logged in as the user in that user's realm.  In both cases, the browser will be redirected to the impersonated user's User Account Management\n"
"page.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/impersonation.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "Any user with the realm's `impersonation` role can impersonate a user.  Please see the <<_admin_permissions,Admin Console Access Control>> chapter\n"
"for more details on assigning administration permissions.\n"
msgstr ""

